                <fr:display-uri>schm-A6LH</fr:display-uri>
                <fr:route>/schm-A6LH/</fr:route>
                <fr:title text="Noetherian and non-Noetherian affine schemes">Noetherian and non-Noetherian affine schemes</fr:title>
                <fr:taxon>Example</fr:taxon>
              </fr:frontmatter>
              <fr:mainmatter>
                <html:p>
  By definition, an <fr:link href="/schm-IFX1/" title="Affine scheme" uri="https://charloced.github.io/schm-IFX1/" display-uri="schm-IFX1" type="local">affine scheme</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\operatorname {Spec} A]]></fr:tex> is Noetherian iff <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex> is <fr:link href="/idem-comm-JOTR/" title="Noetherian distributive lattice" uri="https://charloced.github.io/idem-comm-JOTR/" display-uri="idem-comm-JOTR" type="local">Noetherian</fr:link>.
</html:p>
                <html:p>
  From <fr:link href="/schm-LRJP/" title="The Rieger-Nishimura scheme" uri="https://charloced.github.io/schm-LRJP/" display-uri="schm-LRJP" type="local">Example <fr:contextual-number uri="https://charloced.github.io/schm-LRJP/" display-uri="schm-LRJP" /></fr:link>, <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\operatorname {Spec}\mathbb {H}[x]]]></fr:tex> is <html:em>not</html:em> Noetherian, since <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {H}[x]]]></fr:tex> has infinite ascending elements. In fact, it is <html:em>not</html:em> locally Noetherian either, due to the existance of the focal point <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\bot ]]></fr:tex> of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\operatorname {Spec}\mathbb {H}[x]]]></fr:tex>, whose only open neighbourhood is the entire space. However, the open subscheme <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\operatorname {Spec}\mathbb {H}[x]_+]]></fr:tex> of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\operatorname {Spec}\mathbb {H}[x]]]></fr:tex> described in <fr:link href="/schm-LRJP/" title="The Rieger-Nishimura scheme" uri="https://charloced.github.io/schm-LRJP/" display-uri="schm-LRJP" type="local">Example <fr:contextual-number uri="https://charloced.github.io/schm-LRJP/" display-uri="schm-LRJP" /></fr:link> is locally Noetherian.
</html:p>
                <html:p>
  Dually, from <fr:link href="/schm-DK1B/" title="The dual Rieger-Nishimura scheme" uri="https://charloced.github.io/schm-DK1B/" display-uri="schm-DK1B" type="local">Example <fr:contextual-number uri="https://charloced.github.io/schm-DK1B/" display-uri="schm-DK1B" /></fr:link> we know <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {S}[x]]]></fr:tex> <html:em>is</html:em> Noetherian, hence <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\operatorname {Spec}\mathbb {S}[x]]]></fr:tex> is Noetherian.
</html:p>
              </fr:mainmatter>
