            <fr:title text="Noetherian topological spaces have compact opens">Noetherian topological spaces have compact opens</fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Lemma</fr:taxon>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter><html:p>
  A topological space <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex> is <fr:link href="/topl-AWX1/" title="Noetherian topological spaces" uri="https://charloced.github.io/topl-AWX1/" display-uri="topl-AWX1" type="local">Noetherian</fr:link> iff every open subset of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex> is compact.
</html:p>
 
   
   <fr:tree show-metadata="false" toc="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:authors /><fr:date><fr:year>2025</fr:year><fr:month>6</fr:month><fr:day>11</fr:day></fr:date><fr:taxon>Proof</fr:taxon></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter>
  <html:p>
    If we have an infinite open cover <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\bigcup _{i\in  I}V_I]]></fr:tex> of an open set <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[U]]></fr:tex> in <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex> which does not have a finite subcover, then we may take a well-order on <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[I]]></fr:tex> and define an infinite ascending sequence
    <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[ V_0 \subseteq  V_0 \cup  V_1 \subseteq  \cdots  \bigcup _{\alpha  < i} V_{\alpha } \subseteq  \cdots  ]]></fr:tex>
    This sequence cannot be stationary, otherwise <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[U]]></fr:tex> will have a finite subcover. Hence, taking the complements induces an infinite descending sequence of closed sets.
  </html:p>
  <html:p>
    On the other hand, if every open of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex> is compact, then for any infinite descending sequence of closed sets <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[C_0 \supseteq  C_1 \supseteq  \cdots ]]></fr:tex>, we take their intersection <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\bigcap _{n}C_n]]></fr:tex>. This is a closed set, hence its complement is a compact open. This implies there exists some finite <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[N]]></fr:tex> that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\bigcap _{n\le  N}C_n = \bigcap _{n}C_n]]></fr:tex>, which implies this sequence is stationary.
  </html:p>
</fr:mainmatter></fr:tree>
 
</fr:mainmatter>
